erts]]\n| 56\n| colspan=2|DNF <br>Steering Arm\n|-\n! [[1964 12 Hours of Sebring|1964]]\n| P3+0\n| 1\n| {{Goodyear}}\n|align=\"left\"| [[AC Cobra]]<br>[[Ford Motor Company|Ford]] V8/90\u00b0 2v OHV 7000cc\n|align=\"left\"| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Carroll Shelby International|Shelby American Inc.]]\n|align=\"left\"| {{flagicon|USA}} [[John Morton (racing driver)|John Morton]]\n| 81\n| colspan=2|DNF <br>Blown Engine\n|-\n! [[1965 12 Hours of Sebring|1965]]\n| P+5.0\n| 98\n| {{Goodyear}}\n|align=\"left\"| [[Ford GT40]]<br>[[Ford Motor Company|Ford]] 289 V8/90\u00b0 2v UHV 4727cc\n|align=\"left\"| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Carroll Shelby International|Shelby American Inc.]]\n|align=\"left\"| {{flagicon|NZL}} [[Bruce McLaren]]\n| 192\n| bgcolor=\"#dfdfdf\" | '''2nd'''\n| bgcolor=\"#fbffbf\" | '''1st'''\n|-\n! [[1966 12 Hours of Sebring|1966]]\n| P+5.0\n| 1\n| {{Goodyear}}\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"| [[Ford GT40|Ford GT-X1]]<br>[[Ford Motor Company|Ford]] A V8 OHV 7040cc\n|align=\"left\"| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Carroll Shelby International|Shelby American Inc.]]\n|align=\"left\"| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Lloyd Ruby]]\n| 228\n| bgcolor=\"#fbffbf\" | '''1st'''\n| bgcolor=\"#fbffbf\" | '''1st'''\n|-\n!colspan=\"10\"|{{center|{{small|Source:<ref name=MilesSportsCarResults>{{cite web|title=Complete Archive of Ken Miles|url=https://www.racingsportscars.com/driver/archive/Ken-Miles-GB.html|publisher=Racing Sports Cars|format=[https://www.racingsportscars.com/driver/archive/Ken-Miles-GB.html?page=2 p. 2] [https://www.racingsportscars.com/driver/archive/Ken-Miles-GB.html?page=3 p. 3] [https://www.racingsportscars.com/driver/archive/Ken-Miles-GB.html?page=4 p. 4] [https://www.racingsportscars.com/driver/archive/Ken-Miles-GB.html?page=5 p. 5] [https://www.racingsportscars.com/driver/archive/Ken-Miles-GB.html?page=6 p. 6] [https://www.racingsportscars.com/driver/archive/Ken-Miles-GB.html?page=7 p. 7] [https://www.racingsportscars.com/driver/archive/Ken-Miles-GB.html?page=8 p. 8] [https://www.racingsportscars.com/driver/archive/Ken-Miles-GB.html?page=9 p. 9]|accessdate=18 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>}}}}\n|}\n\n== Personal life ==\nKen Miles was married to Mollie and had a son, Peter Miles. When Ken died while testing a prototype car in 1966, Peter, who witnessed his father's death,<ref name=\"pajiba\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pajiba.com/film_reviews/ford-v-ferrari-what-happened-to-ken-miles-son-peter.php|title='Ford v. Ferrari': What Happened to Ken Miles' Son, Peter?|first=Dustin|last=Rowles|date=2019-11-16|accessdate=2019-11-25|df=dmy-all}}</ref> was almost 15. A few months after Ken's death, Peter went to work for Ken's friend Dick Troutman at the Troutman and Barnes custom car shop in Culver City, CA. Peter stayed at the workshop for four years. In 1986, Peter joined [[PPI Motorsports|Precision Performance Inc.]] (PPI), starting as a fabricator and then a mechanic before becoming the crew chief. Peter was the crew chief for [[Ivan Stewart]] when Stewart won the 1991 [[Mint 400|Nissan 400]] in Nevada.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-1991-06-06-sp-55-story.html|title=MOTOR RACING : Miles Has Taken His Own Route to Father's Sport|date=1991-06-06|website=Los Angeles Times|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-16}}</ref> In a 2019 interview with Le Mans, Peter revealed that the last time he went to Le Mans was in 1965 with his father Ken, and he has not returned since.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lemans.org/app_dev.php/en/news/le-mans-66-ford-v-ferrari-peter-miles-talks-about-his-father-ken-miles/52849|title=\"Le Mans 66\" (\"Ford v Ferrari\") \u2013 Peter Miles talks about his father, Ken Miles|website=lemans.org|language=fr|access-date=2019-11-16}}</ref>\n\nPeter is currently an executive administrator of a vintage car collection belonging to [[William E. Connor II]]., believed to be valued at over $80 million, which included a [[Ferrari 250 GTO]], considered by respected Ferrari historian Marcel Massini as the best example of all 36 built.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://argonautnews.com/gentlemen-start-your-engines/|title=Gentlemen, start your engines|website=The Argonaut Newsweekly|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-11-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/2000/12/11/1214vehiclesate.html|title=Marcel Massini, Ferrari Historian|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=2019-12-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.barchetta.cc/english/All.Ferraris/Detail/4293GT.250GTO.htm|title=250 GTO s/n 4293GT|website=www.barchetta.cc|access-date=2019-12-04}}</ref>\n\n==In popular culture==\nMiles is portrayed by [[Christian Bale]] in the 2019 film ''[[Ford v Ferrari]]'' (released under the title ''Le Mans '66'' in some parts of Europe)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/james-mangold-next-film-ford-ferrari-logan-1202687686/ |title=James Mangold to Direct Ford vs. Ferrari Film as 'Logan' Follow-Up |publisher=variety.com |accessdate=5 February 2018}}</ref> Miles' wife Mollie and his son Peter are portrayed by [[Caitriona Balfe]] and [[Noah Jupe]], respectively.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/outlander-a-quiet-place-stars-join-ford-ferrari-movie-1114517 |title='Outlander' Star Caitriona Balfe, 'Quiet Place' Breakout Noah Jupe Join Ford vs. Ferrari Movie |publisher=hollywoodreporter.com |accessdate=23 May 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/ford-v-ferrari-trailer-matt-damon-christian-bale-design-race-car-1214837|title='Ford v. Ferrari' Trailer: Matt Damon, Christian Bale Team Up to Design Race Car|publisher=hollywoodreporter.com |date=2 June 2019 |accessdate=3 June 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.saac.com Shelby American Automobile Club World Registry of Cobras & GT40s]\n* {{findagrave|92639918}}\n\n{{24 Hours of Daytona winners}}\n{{12 Hours of Sebring winners}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Miles, Ken}}\n[[Category:1918 births]]\n[[Category:1966 deaths]]\n[[Category:English expatriates in the United States]]\n[[Category:English racing drivers]]\n[[Category:Racing drivers killed while racing]]\n[[Category:Sports deaths in California]]\n[[Category:Accidental deaths in California]]\n[[Category:24 Hours of Le Mans drivers]]\n[[Category:24 Hours of Daytona drivers]]\n[[Category:World Sportscar Championship drivers]]\n[[Category:12 Hours of Sebring drivers]]\n", "name_user": "Daksh2k", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ken_Miles"}
