ue-080158219.html\n}}\n\n{{Ohlone}}\n{{Indigenous peoples of California}}\n\n{{Good article}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ohlone People}}\n[[Category:Ohlone| ]]\n[[Category:California Mission Indians]]\n[[Category:History of Monterey County, California]]\n[[Category:History of San Benito County, California]]\n[[Category:History of San Francisco]]\n[[Category:History of San Mateo County, California]]\n[[Category:History of Santa Clara County, California]]\n[[Category:History of Santa Cruz County, California]]\n[[Category:History of the San Francisco Bay Area]]\n[[Category:Native American tribes in California]]\n", "name_user": "2601:647:ca00:9b80:51b0:3228:3f4e:eb7c", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ohlone"}
{"title_page": "1928 Yugoslav Football Championship", "text_new": "The '''1928 National Championship''' ([[Serbo-Croatian|Serbo-Croato-Slovenian]]: Dr\u017eavno prvenstvo 1928. / \u0414\u0440\u0436\u0430\u0432\u043d\u043e \u043f\u0440\u0432\u0435\u043d\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e 1928.) proclaimed Gradanski Zagreb once again as the reigning champions, with Hajduk and BSK following closely behind.\n\n==Qualifications==\nThe champions of the Belgrade, Split and Zagreb subassociations qualified directly to the final phase, while the second place teams of Belgrade and Zagreb, along with the champions of the rest of the subassociations, played a two-legged elimination round.\n\nThe representatives were:\n\n*Subassociation of Belgrade: [[SK Jugoslavija]] (qualified directly) and [[BSK Belgrade]]\n*Subassociation of Zagreb: [[Gra\u0111anski Zagreb]] (qualified directly) and [[HA\u0160K]]\n*Subassociation of Split: [[HNK Hajduk Split|Hajduk Split]] (qualified directly)\n*Subassociation of Ljubljana: [[A\u0160K Primorje|Primorje]]\n*Subassociation of Osijek: Gra\u0111anski Osijek\n*Subassociation of Sarajevo: [[NK SA\u0160K Napredak|SA\u0160K]]\n*Subassociation of Subotica: [[SAND Subotica]]\n\nQualifying round:\n*BSK \u2013 Gra\u0111anski Osijek 6:1, 6:1\n*HA\u0160K \u2013 SAND 6:1, 4:2\n*Primorje \u2013 SA\u0160K 4:3, 2:3, extra match: 2:3\n\nThe qualifiers were played in both, home and away matches, and were played on June 10 the first leg, and on June 17 the second.  Primorje and SA\u0160K needed an extra match which was played on June 18 in Sarajevo.<ref>Milorad Siji\u0107: \"Fudbal u Kraljevini Jugoslaviji\", pags. 57-58</ref>\n\n==League==\n{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|res_col_header=Q\n|winpoints=2\n|use_goal_ratio=y\n\n|team1=GRZ|name_GRZ=[[Gra\u0111anski Zagreb|Gra\u0111anski]]\n|team2=HAJ|name_HAJ=[[Hajduk Split]]\n|team3=BSK|name_BSK=[[BSK Beograd|BSK]]\n|team4=S\u0160K|name_S\u0160K=[[SA\u0160K]]\n|team5=H\u0160K|name_H\u0160K=[[HA\u0160K]]\n|team6=JUG|name_JUG=[[SK Jugoslavija]]\n|win_GRZ=4|draw_GRZ=1|loss_GRZ=0|gf_GRZ=12|ga_GRZ=3\n|win_HAJ=2|draw_HAJ=2|loss_HAJ=1|gf_HAJ=13|ga_HAJ=7\n|win_BSK=3|draw_BSK=0|loss_BSK=2|gf_BSK=12|ga_BSK=15\n|win_S\u0160K=2|draw_S\u0160K=1|loss_S\u0160K=2|gf_S\u0160K=10|ga_S\u0160K=7\n|win_H\u0160K=1|draw_H\u0160K=0|loss_H\u0160K=4|gf_H\u0160K=10|ga_H\u0160K=16\n|win_JUG=0|draw_JUG=2|loss_JUG=3|gf_JUG=5|ga_JUG=14\n\n|col_MC=yellow1|text_MC=Qualification for [[1928 Mitropa Cup|Mitropa Cup]]\n|result1=MC|result3=MC\n|update=complete|source=[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesj/joeghist.html rsssf.com]\n\n|hth_HAJ=It is unclear why Hajduk Split was ranked above BSK Beograd, as the results show that BSK had more wins than Hajduk, although they were still tied. One argument is that the goal differential determined that, however goal difference should only be taken into account if the two teams are equal in wins, draws and losses.\n|hth_BSK=HAJ\n\n|hth_S\u0160K= [[Politika]] reported that on the second round, SA\u0160K was suspended for having abandoned the match in the 8th minute of the second half when playing against BSK.  Because of that, they were suspended for 3 months, however they were allowed to play the three matches left because none of them would have influence in the title.\n}}\n\n==Top scorers==\nFinal goalscoring position, number of goals, player/players and club.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=mU7S_yexUFUC&pg=PA251&dq=bsk+jugoslavija&hl=pt-PT&sa=X&ei=3SQ4T93cG-Kp0QWk4e2PAg&ved=0CE0QuwUwAw#v=onepage&q=bsk%20jugoslavija&f=false Gola istina: kraljevi strelaca] by \u017divko Bojani\u0107, pag. 24 {{in lang|sr}}</ref>\n*1 - 8 goals - [[Ljubo Ben\u010di\u0107]] (Hajduk Split)\n*2 - 5 goals - Branko Zinaja (HA\u0160K)\n*3 - 3 goals - [[Dragutin Babi\u0107]], [[Slavin Cindri\u0107]] (both Gra\u0111anski Zagreb), [[Kuzman Sotirovi\u0107]], Milorad Dragi\u010devi\u0107 (both BSK Belgrade)\n\n===Champions===\n'''H\u0160K GRA\u0110ANSKI''' (coach: [[Imre Pozsonyi]])<br><br>\n[[Maksimilijan Mihal\u010di\u0107]]<br>Zvonimir Gmajni\u010dki<br>Franz Mantler<br>[[Rudolf Hitrec]]<br>Piki\u0107<br>Viktor Mihaljevi\u0107<br>Miho Remec<br>Nikola Babi\u0107<br>[[Dragutin Babi\u0107]]<br>Emil Per\u0161ka<br>[[Slavin Cindri\u0107]]<br>[[Franjo Giler]]\n\n==See also==\n*[[Yugoslav Cup]]\n*[[Yugoslav League Championship]]\n*[[Football Association of Yugoslavia]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesj/joeghist.html Yugoslavia Domestic Football Full Tables]\n\n{{Yugoslav First League}}\n{{1928\u201329 in European football (UEFA)}}\n\n[[Category:1928\u201329 in Yugoslavian football|1]]\n[[Category:Yugoslav Football Championship]]\n", "text_old": "The '''1928 National Championship''' ([[Serbo-Croatian|Serbo-Croato-Slovenian]]: Dr\u017eavno prvenstvo 1928. / \u0414\u0440\u0436\u0430\u0432\u043d\u043e \u043f\u0440\u0432\u0435\u043d\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e 1928.) proclaimed Gradanski Zagreb once again as the reigning champions, with Hajduk and BSK following closely behind.\n\n==Qualifications==\nThe champions of the Belgrade, Split and Zagreb subassociations qualified directly to the final phase, while the second place teams of Belgrade and Zagreb, along with the champions of the rest of the subassociations, played a two-legged elimination round.\n\nThe representatives were:\n\n*Subassociation of Belgrade: [[SK Jugoslavija]] (qualified directly) and [[BSK Belgrade]]\n*Subassociation of Zagreb: [[Gra\u0111anski Zagreb]] (qualified directly) and [[HA\u0160K]]\n*Subassociation of Split: [[HNK Hajduk Split|Hajduk Split]] (qualified directly)\n*Subassociation of Ljubljana: [[A\u0160K Primorje|Primorje]]\n*Subassociation of Osijek: Gra\u0111anski Osijek\n*Subassociation of Sarajevo: [[NK SA\u0160K Napredak|SA\u0160K]]\n*Subassociation of Subotica: [[SAND Subotica]]\n\nQualifying round:\n*BSK \u2013 Gra\u0111anski Osijek 6:1, 6:1\n*HA\u0160K \u2013 SAND 6:1, 4:2\n*Primorje \u2013 SA\u0160K 4:3, 2:3, extra match: 2:3\n\nThe qualifiers were played in both, home and away matches, and were played on June 10 the first leg, and on June 17 the second.  Primorje and SA\u0160K needed an extra match which was played on June 18 in Sarajevo.<ref>Milorad Siji\u0107: \"Fudbal u Kraljevini Jugoslaviji\", pags. 57-58</ref>\n\n==League==\n{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|res_col_header=Q\n|winpoints=2\n|use_goal_ratio=y\n\n|team1=GRZ|name_GRZ=[[Gra\u0111anski Zagreb|Gra\u0111anski]]\n|team2=HAJ|name_HAJ=[[Hajduk Split]]\n|team3=BSK|name_BSK=[[BSK Beograd|BSK]]\n|team4=S\u0160K|name_S\u0160K=[[SA\u0160K]]\n|team5=H\u0160K|name_H\u0160K=[[HA\u0160K]]\n|team6=JUG|name_JUG=[[SK Jugoslavija]]\n|win_GRZ=4|draw_GRZ=1|loss_GRZ=0|gf_GRZ=12|ga_GRZ=3\n|win_HAJ=2|draw_HAJ=2|loss_HAJ=1|gf_HAJ=13|ga_HAJ=7\n|win_BSK=3|draw_BSK=0|loss_BSK=2|gf_BSK=12|ga_BSK=15\n|win_S\u0160K=2|draw_S\u0160K=1|loss_S\u0160K=2|gf_S\u0160K=10|ga_S\u0160K=7\n|win_H\u0160K=1|draw_H\u0160K=0|loss_H\u0160K=4|gf_H\u0160K=10|ga_H\u0160K=16\n|win_JUG=0|draw_JUG=2|loss_JUG=3|gf_JUG=5|ga_JUG=14\n\n|col_MC=yellow1|text_MC=[[Mitropa Cup 1928|Mitropa Cup]]\n|result1=MC|result3=MC\n|update=complete|source=[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesj/joeghist.html rsssf.com]\n\n|hth_HAJ=It is unclear why Hajduk Split was ranked above BSK Beograd, as the results show that BSK had more wins than Hajduk, although they were still tied. One argument is that the goal differential determined that, however goal difference should only be taken into account if the two teams are equal in wins, draws and losses.\n|hth_BSK=HAJ\n\n|hth_S\u0160K= [[Politika]] reported that on the second round, SA\u0160K was suspended for having abandoned the match in the 8th minute of the second half when playing against BSK.  Because of that, they were suspended for 3 months, however they were allowed to play the three matches left because none of them would have influence in the title.\n}}\n==Top scorers==\nFinal goalscoring position, number of goals, player/players and club.<ref>[https://books.